reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little lamps. Shade needs assembled. USB ports 10w total. Happy with these!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this two pack for my night stands. Admittedly they were slightly smaller than I was expecting but thats not the fault of the product as the dimensions are in the product description, so that's on me.Assemble was very easy, took maybe 5 minutes each. I was a little surprised the lamp shade needed assembled too, but again was easy enough. It has a small and larger metal right that the top and bottom of the lamp shade clip onto around the right. The two seams come together with velcro. This leaves a visible overlap seam thats not flush. If this bothers you, it's something to consider. However, in my case, I just turned it so the seam faces the wall and is hidden from view.The included bulb has 3 stages and gets pretty bright. These two on at full brightness can illuminate my 20x30' bedroom at night.The touch feature is great for easy on/off at night. The USB ports work well. From what I can tell the USB-A and USB-C port can output 10w combined total, not each. So don't expect to fast charge your phone, but if you plug it in before bed its enough to full charge your phone in a few hours.The USB-A port isn't very deep. It works fine but be mindful of this. Whereas you would normally expect the usb connector to fully seat in a usb port, it doesn't with these lamps, it goes in about half way. It still works to charge, I'm mentioning this though as you don't want to force it and potentially break the port.Overall very happy with these so far, and definitely a great value for the price.
